-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell I7 (matrix row 21b): IMPORTER shadow in VALUE position over
-- LIVE-IMPL elements.  The importer twin of d4b (row 10): a value-position shadow
-- denotes the standalone ALWAYS, so `Box` elements mistype against the standalone's
-- domain (`Int -> Int`) and this is a LOCATED REJECT -- never a silent dispatch.
--
-- #411: was the SILENT half.  check reported zero diagnostics, and run AND build both
-- printed [1, 2] -- all three engines agreeing on the answer the spec forbids.  That
-- is the S7 trap in its purest form: no differential gate could ever have seen it,
-- which is why this cell is pinned on the located REJECT and not on agreement.
-- Expected: check/run/build all REJECT with `Type mismatch: Int vs Box`.
import prov.{size}

data Box = Box Int

interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box n) = n

main = println (map size [Box 1, Box 2])
